data.name: realPlayerHealthCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Changes the player's health to be realistic and to match that of PMC bots and Scavs. Use in combination with "Realistic Ballistics".
NOTE: You must disable this AND select "Revert HP to Default" otherwise your health will not change back. You don't need to do this if you're going to use another mod to change your health.
It is NOT recommended to turn this off, it is balanced around changes to ballistics, and turning it off may cause unforseen issues. This is only an option for those who want to raise their health using another mod to make the game easier.

data.name: masteryCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Changes what weapons fall into what Mastery categories. Weapons that have similar controls or reload operation are in the same category. For most weapons, mastery will come a lot quicker because of this.

data.name: recoilAttOverhaulCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Enables the complete overhaul of recoil, ballistics and attachments. See the mod's overview page on the hub for details. You can further configure the overhaul in-game, press F12 to open the config menu for mods.
NOTE: some of the changes made by this overhaul are balanaced around the changes made to ammo stats, it is recommended to use in combination with 'Realistic Ballistics'.
IF YOU WANT TO DISABLE THIS FEATURE YOU MUST DELETE THE REALISMMOD.DLL FROM YOUR BEPINEX/PLUGINS FOLDER. OTHERWISE YOUR GAME WILL CRASH!

data.name: buffHelmetsCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Buffs helmets and faceshields by raising their armor level by 1. Their blunt throughput has been modified to compensate. Not carefully balanced, just for those that want a slightly less hardcore experience.

data.name: headgearConflictsCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Ensures Bots Spawn with NVGs Correctly And Makes some masks and headgear conflict to prevent bots from looking cursed, these are items that clip badly.
If disabled, bots will sometimes spawn with NVG mounts but the NVG missing.

data.name: realBallisticsCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Enables Armor and Ammo changes, the core of Realism Mod. This will change the health of bot PMCs and Scavs to be balanced with these changes. Also changes the ammo and armor of starter profiles to reflect these changes.
NOTE: Ammo has been balanced with the changes made by the 'Recoil, Ballistics and Attachment' overhaul in mind, it is not recommended to use the overhaul with this option disabled.

data.name: medChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Enables changes to medical items to be more hardcore. Only stims, surgery kits and new craftable makeshift medical kits will restore HP. Most meds now have debuffs to simulate the wound trauma from getting shot and the negative effects of tourniquets on the body. See the mod overview page for details.

data.name: bossSpawnCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Boss/Rogue/Raider spawn chances increase as you level up, allows bosses to spawn in more parts of the map, adds chance for Raiders and Rogues to spawn on more maps, increases Raider trigger spawns to 100%.

data.name: pmcTypeCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Changes the odds and available behaviour templates that PMCs can use. The types available and their odds changes based on the level of the PMC, the map and the time of day. These templates are based on existing bot types, such as scavs, bosses, rogues, raiders etc.
NOTE: Will only take effect if 'Bot Changes' is enabled. PMCs using different templates is a feature of SPT AKI, this option just changes what templates are used and how/when.

data.name: pmcDifficultyCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Raises PMC and Boss difficulty. Will just simply set bosses and PMC from 'AsOnline' to a higher difficulty settings (Hard or Impossible).
NOTE: This option will only take effect if 'Bot Changes' is enabled. It's not recommended to use this option if you are using mods that change AI behaviour. .

data.name: bossDifficultyCheck.ToolTip
data.value:

NOTE: This option will only take effect if 'Bot Changes' is enabled. It's not recommended to use this option if you are using mods that change AI behaviour.

NOTE: This option will only take effect if 'Bot Changes' is enabled. It's not recommended to use this option if you are using mods that change AI behaviour.

data.name: realBossHealthCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Bot health settings. If set to true, these bot types will have the same health as the player. If false, they will have default EFT health pools.
NOTE: 'Realistic Ballistics' option must be true for this to take effect. If realism is false, all bots will have defualt health.

data.name: tieredFleaCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If Enabled the fleamarket will unlock progressivly by category or subcategory of item based on the player's level. There are 7 tiers in total, the final one being a 'full unlock'. Most items are no longer blacklisted from the flea.

data.name: traderChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Enables dynamic changes to trader stock and item availability. Items can be out of stock completely, and will always have limited stock if it's available.
Also changes the categorie of items that traders will buy to make more sense, makes Fence hace less offers and increases the cost of Therapist's healing.

data.name: airdropChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If enabled airdrops will have 'types' (medical supplies, food, ammo, etc.) and will only have items of that type. Different types have different rarity, airdrop types will be rerolled when starting the game or at the end of raids.

data.name: convMultLabel.ToolTip
data.value: Also Known As 'Auto Compensation', This Is The Speed At Which The Gun Comes Under Control. In This Mod Convergence Only Works This Way For Semi Auto, In Full Auto Convergence Dictates The Overall Amount Of Recoil Climb And How Snappy It Is. Basically, Lower = More Recoil That Is More Floaty.

data.name: horzRecMultLabel.ToolTip
data.value: Horizontal Recoil. Horizontal Recoil In EFT Is Actually The Front/Rear Recoil Impulse. With 'Recoil Crank' Enabled More Horizontal Recoil = More Recoil Into The Shoulder, If Disabled Recoil Will Go Forward Instead.
